==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ironsides
<hw>I"ron*sides"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A cuirassier or
cuirassiers; also, hardy veteran soldiers; -- applied specifically to
Cromwell's cavalry.</def></p>

<p><cs><col><b>Old Ironsides</b></col>. <fld>(U. S. Hist.)</fld> <cd>A
nickname for the <ship>U.S.S. Constitution</ship>, a sailing ship which
fought in the American Revolutionary war, and now functions as a
floating museum in Boston harbor. It was given its nickname because
cannonballs bounced off its hard wooden sides.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ironsmith</ent>⟦br⟧
